---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service - Menu Volume"
  description="Terms of Service for Menu Volume app"
>
  <main class="min-h-screen bg-white">
    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-orange-600 to-red-600">
      <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-16 text-center">
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-white mb-4">
          Terms of Service
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl text-orange-100">
          Menu Volume
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Content -->
    <div class="container mx-auto px-6 py-16 max-w-4xl">
      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">
          Last updated: September 1, 2025
        </div>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            By downloading, installing, or using Menu Volume ("the App"), you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service ("Terms"). If you do not agree to these Terms, do not use the App.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">2. Description of Service</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Menu Volume is a macOS application that allows users to control system volume and Apple Music volume independently. The App provides:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
            <li>System volume control via menu bar interface</li>
            <li>Independent Apple Music volume control</li>
            <li>Menu bar integration with live sliders</li>
            <li>Launch at login option</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">3. System Requirements</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            The App requires:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
            <li>macOS 10.15 (Catalina) or later</li>
            <li>Apple Music app (for optional Apple Music control features)</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">4. Privacy and Data</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            The App operates with minimal data collection:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
            <li>No personal data is collected or transmitted to external servers</li>
            <li>Apple Music integration requires automation permission when enabled</li>
            <li>All settings and configurations are stored locally on your device</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">5. Permissions</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            The App may request the following permissions:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
            <li><strong>Apple Music Automation:</strong> Optional permission for controlling Apple Music volume</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            You can revoke these permissions at any time through macOS System Preferences.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">6. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            The App is provided "as is" without warranties of any kind. We are not liable for any damages arising from the use of the App, including but not limited to:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
            <li>Hardware compatibility issues</li>
            <li>System audio interruptions</li>
            <li>Data loss or corruption</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">7. User Responsibilities</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            Users are responsible for:
          </p>
          <ul class="list-disc list-inside text-gray-700 mb-4 space-y-2">
            <li>Backing up system preferences if desired</li>
            <li>Using the App in accordance with these Terms</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">8. Updates and Changes</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            We may update the App and these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the App after updates constitutes acceptance of any changes. Major updates will be distributed through the Mac App Store.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">9. Termination</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            You may stop using the App at any time by uninstalling it from your device. These Terms will remain in effect until terminated by either party.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">10. Contact Information</h2>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            If you have questions about these Terms or the App, please contact us through the Mac App Store.
          </p>
        </section>

        <div class="mt-16 p-6 bg-gray-50 rounded-xl">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
            These Terms of Service are effective as of September 1, 2025. By using Menu Volume, you acknowledge that you have read and understood these Terms and agree to be bound by them.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <Footer />
  </main>
</Layout>